{
  "stem": "26142.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In-- in September, September the 1st, which was, I think, on a-- on a high holiday of the Rosh Hashanah, 1940.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] And September the 1st, 1940, the Germans attacked Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had made a secret agreement with the Soviet Union with the other monster, Stalin.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That, of course, that was a secret.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody knew about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, Poland was overrun by Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And under the secret agreement between Poland and Russia, the Russians got the part of Ukraine and the Poles-- and the Germans got the rest of-- of Poland.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So all of a sudden, in 1940, we became neighbors to the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because they came all the way to-- to Torun in 1940.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In a-- in a way-- in a way we were-- we were happy that at least that part of the Polish jury was more or less-- or less safe from physical destruction.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because that-- that consisted of the cities, large cities like Lvov, Lemburg, Stryi, [INAUDIBLE]-- those were large Jewish communities that fell under the Soviet-- under the Soviet rule.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So the Germans and the-- and the Russians divided up Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we became-- Torun became the border.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Hungarians started sending in troops into the-- into the-- to the city in Torun by the border, was choked full of Hungarian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took away the-- the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They took away the Hebrew school, and the-- the-- the houses.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If you had an extra room or two, if you had four rooms, they would take two rooms.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They came-- while they became the-- the neighbors of the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they started-- that was-- started building fortifications in 1940.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
